<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: BUILDERS/DEVELOPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Keith A. Johnson, chief operating officer, has been named president of the 
Firestone Co. He will maintain his offices at both the firm's San Diego 
division headquarters and at Newport Beach corporate headquarters. Johnson 
co-founded the company with Peter Ochs in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Vliss has been promoted to executive vice president for Inco Homes, based 
in Upland. Vliss will chair the company's executive committee meetings and 
become more involved in overall activities. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego-based Nielsen Construction Co. has promoted Jeffrey E. Platt to 
senior vice president. Platt will continue as chief financial officer, 
treasurer and assistant secretary of the board. 
</P>
<P>
At Calabasas-based Griffin Homes, Tak Fujii is new senior vice president of 
corporate operations and Charles H. Fedalen Jr. is the company's vice president 
and general counsel. Fedalen is also corporate secretary. 
</P>
<P>
Stephen P. Wallace is chief financial officer at A-M Homes, Santa Barbara. 
Wallace will work with financial institutions and oversee the company's 
budgeting, accounting and tax policies. 
</P>
<P>
Bret Magpiong has joined Cuesta Properties Inc., Irvine, as vice president of 
finance and investments. Magpiong will lead the real estate division and 
supervise property acquisition and development. 
</P>
<P>
The Southern California division of Leisure Technology has named Michael Poltl 
vice president of finance and administration. Poltl supervises financial 
reporting, banking relationships and management of the Oceanside-based 
division. 
</P>
<P>
Bren Co.'s new director of land development in its San Diego division is E. 
Dale Gleed. He will prepare site budgets, and analyze land investment 
opportunities. 
</P>
<P>
Connie Millsap has joined Los Angeles-based Environmental Contracting Corp. as 
vice president of business development. The general contractor specializes in 
tenant improvements and office build outs. 
</P>
<P>
Trammell Crow Co. in Irvine has announced that Susan B. Whittaker will plan 
development of the firm's Park Place project. 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Samuel E. Haynes, executive vice president of Irvine-based Bramalea 
California, Inc., has been elected to the 1990 national board of directors of 
the National Assn. of Industrial and Office Parks. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Property Managers 
</P>
<P>
Victoria Partnership in Rancho Dominguez has a new vice president of property 
management: Patrick H. Hanrahan. He manages and leases the Victoria 
Partnership, Carson Estate Co. and Carson Dominguez Properties portfolios. 
Hanrahan is an eighth generation descendant of Juan Jose Dominguez, who was 
awarded the 76,000-acre Rancho San Pedro land grant in 1784. 
</P>
<P>
Richard P. Welles, president of the Building Owners and Managers Assn. of 
Greater Los Angeles, has joined Manufacturers Real Estate as property manager 
of its 35-story 865 South Figueroa Street office building, under construction 
in downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Lilly Lee, chairman of Lilly Enterprises, Inc. and Lilly Property Management 
Co., was named 1989 Businesswoman of the Year by the Asian Business League of 
Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Clive Graham Jr., 1986 president of the Greater Los Angeles Chapter 
of the Institute of Real Estate Management, has received the 1989 Henry G. 
Beaumont Certified Property Manager of the Year award. Graham is president of 
Graham Management Corp. in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Marketing 
</P>
<P>
Maria Mitchell-Schaeffer has been promoted to vice president and regional 
director of the Mitchell Co.. She oversees marketing and sales operations of 
the company's northern region. The Calabasas-based firm sells and markets new 
residential communities throughout the Southland. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Civil Engineers 
</P>
<P>
The Keith Cos., headquartered in Costa Mesa, has hired Joseph J. Chesler to be 
principal planner, specializing in public agency services. Keith Lee Ludowitz 
has become principal planner in the firm's North Counties division, based in 
Woodland Hills. 
</P>
<P>
James W. May Jr. has been named senior project manager of the San Juan 
Capistrano office of VTN Southwest Inc., a San Diego-based land planning, civil 
engineering and surveying firm. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Title Firms 
</P>
<P>
World Title Co. has chosen Guido Schenkhuizen, a corporate vice president, to 
be operations manager for the company's Arcadia office. Jim Belardi has been 
appointed vice president and San Bernardino and Riverside County sales manager. 
Belardi will continue as San Bernardino County operations manager. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Law Firms 
</P>
<P>
Robert Smylie and Gary Leven have announced their new partnership, Smylie &amp; 
Leven, in Century City. The firm specializes in real estate law. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Brokers 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Ben Cheng is the new president of the Los Angeles chapter of 
Certified Commercial Investment Members. Cheng has been a real estate 
instructor in UCLA and UC Irvine extensions. He created Ben Cheng Seminars. 
</P>
<P>
Gill A. Barnett II has been promoted to sales and marketing director of Collins 
Fuller Corp., headquartered in Newport Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
